New Records: Victor Wembanyama set a career-high with 50 points
Wembanyama is the fourth-youngest player to score 50 points
Wembanyama was 8 for 16 on three-pointers, establishing a career-high
Key Match Events: Wembanyama started quickly against the Wizards, draining three-pointers from 25 and 28 feet as the Spurs raced to a 13-3 lead
Wembanyama had 24 points in the first half, his highest production in a first half
Post-Match Reflections: Wembanyama, the top pick in the 2023 NBA draft, wondered when he will do better even as his historic night led San Antonio to a 139-130 victory over the Washington Wizards
Miscellaneous Highlights: Wembanyama is the first player in league history with 20 three-pointers and 25 blocks over a six-game span
Others: Wembanyama's performance left his teammates and the opposition in awe
The Spurs host Los Angeles Lakers on Friday night in the final game of a five-game homestand
